{"id": "EUVD-2025-13962", "enisaUuid": "13e40bd8-32da-3bbd-8d1d-da4a08d2237f", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nriscv: uprobes: Add missing fence.i after building the XOL buffer\n\nThe XOL (execute out-of-line) buffer is used to single-step the\nreplaced instruction(s) for uprobes. The RISC-V port was missing a\nproper fence.i (i$ flushing) after constructing the XOL buffer, which\ncan result in incorrect execution of stale/broken instructions.\n\nThis was found running the BPF selftests \"test_progs:\nuprobe_autoattach, attach_probe\" on the Spacemit K1/X60, where the\nuprobes tests randomly blew up.", "datePublished": "2025-05-08T09:30:25", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-10T18:30:31", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37822", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1dbb95a36499374c51b47ee8ae258a8862c20978", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7d1d19a11cfbfd8bae1d89cc010b2cc397cd0c48", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bcf6d3158c5902d92b6d62335af4422b7bf7c4e2"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37822", "GHSA-jc2j-hqm3-7764"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0d321265-dc9d-3f4b-9ca6-e0c6e17abca8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "2dfe7e58-ba3f-3319-8b68-64a52fbf4022", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.26"}, {"id": "3ebe8ae5-9075-3b31-ad03-ce18d576c90e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15-rc4"}, {"id": "61f2795c-e87d-38a9-b7c7-934bcf16b308", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "74784081aac8a0f3636965fc230e2d3b7cc123c6 <bcf6d3158c5902d92b6d62335af4422b7bf7c4e2"}, {"id": "a7f4da9b-8634-3e1a-b6c0-259bfb4a5d7f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "74784081aac8a0f3636965fc230e2d3b7cc123c6 <7d1d19a11cfbfd8bae1d89cc010b2cc397cd0c48"}, {"id": "ec2dbacf-27fe-3062-8b86-243985c7ed59", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.5"}, {"id": "f0ba7673